actual_description: The rental transaction is created, printed, and stored.
Bar code Ids for each tape are entered, and video information from inventory is displayed.
Customers select at least one video for rental.
Each customer gets an id card from ABC for identification purposes.
Any past-due amount must be paid before new tapes can be rented.
The customer signs the rental form, takes the tapes, and leaves.
Change is calculated and displayed.
Money is collected, and the amount is entered into the system.
The rental transaction is displayed, and the tape is marked with the return date.
The customer s account number is entered to retrieve customer data and create an order.
The maximum number of tapes a customer can have outstanding on the rental is 20.
When all tape Ids are entered, the system computes the total bill.
If past-due amounts are owed, they can be paid at this time; or the clerk can select an option that updates the rental with the return date and calculates past-due fees.
Any outstanding video rentals are displayed with the amount due on each tape and the total amount due.
The video inventory file is updated.
This id card has a bar code that can be read with the bar code reader.
